body:
The following will see 1 negedge on `reset`, instead of the expected 2. Specifically the one at time 0 is missing. I believe this is well defined and should just work, there are a lot of sloppy testbenches out there that rely on this (or worse, a x->0 negedge, but that's another matter).

```systemverilog
module top;

  logic reset = 1'b1;

  initial begin
    reset = 1'b0;  // No negedge here
    #10;
    reset = 1'b1;
    #10;
    reset = 1'b0;  // Negedge here
    $finish;
  end

  always @(negedge reset) $display("Got negedge at %0t", $time);

endmodule
```

